choices.text: There is a sequence a that consists of n integers a_1, a_2, ..., a_{n}. Let's denote f(l, r, x) the number of indices k such that: l   k   r and a_{k} = x. His task is to calculate the number of pairs of indicies i, j (1   i < j   n) such that f(1, i, a_{i}) > f(j, n, a_{j}). Help Pashmak with the test.
